    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined tray (or two!)</p><p>Season the<strong> </strong>salmon<strong> </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and spoon the <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong> over the top evenly</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 14-15 min or until the salmon is cooked through – this is your <strong>sweet chilli salmon</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
